EQUINE HERPESVIRUS - NORTH AMERICA (18): USA (NORTH DAKOTA) HORSE
*****************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Mon 1 Jul 2019 4:34 PM CDT
Source: San Francisco Chronicle, Associated Press (AP) report [edited]
https://www.sfchronicle.com/news/article/North-Dakota-sees-1st-case-of-horse-disease-this-14065214.php


The North Dakota Department of Agriculture said Mon 1 Jul 2019 a horse has confirmed positive for the neurologic disease associated with equine herpesvirus-1, or EHV-1.

The horse is receiving veterinary care in McKenzie county.

In the last few months, EHV-1 cases have been identified in several US states and Canadian provinces.

North Dakota Agriculture Commissioner Doug Goehring says many horses will be moving to events around the region this summer [2019]. He says owners should take care when co-mingling horses to minimize chances of horses contracting the disease.

EHV-1 can be spread through the air, contaminated equipment, clothing, and hands.

The virus is highly infectious and contagious among horses but poses no threat to humans.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Vaccination can reduce shedding and may lessen the severity of the neurological form. If you have not vaccinated, please protect your horse as best possible by doing so.

We wish the affected animals a speedy recovery and good health to those animals exposed. - Mod.TG

